00:39:21.950 --> 00:39:23.630
And I know at lunchtime
they have issues

00:39:23.630 --> 00:39:24.880
that they keep having to move.

00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:28.030
And I think it's
detrimental to the people,

00:39:28.030 --> 00:39:30.890
ultimately, in terms of choice.

00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:33.090
ADAM SOBEL: Yeah,
I mean, I think

00:39:33.090 --> 00:39:35.889
it's the council member Steve
Fulop there is kind of--

00:39:35.889 --> 00:39:36.930
AUDIENCE: He's the mayor.

00:39:36.930 --> 00:39:38.200
ADAM SOBEL: Is he the mayor now?

00:39:38.200 --> 00:39:38.825
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:39:38.825 --> 00:39:40.410
ADAM SOBEL: OK, when
I was in Hoboken,

00:39:40.410 --> 00:39:41.784
and he was just
a council member.

00:39:41.784 --> 00:39:44.380
AUDIENCE: Former councilman.

00:39:44.380 --> 00:39:48.777
ADAM SOBEL: I mean, he doesn't
like food trucks either.

00:39:48.777 --> 00:39:50.360
He wears the big
pants in Jersey City.

00:39:52.975 --> 00:39:56.220
But Two Boots guy,
if you're listening,

00:39:56.220 --> 00:39:58.960
I challenge you to a
rap battle or something.

00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:01.250
We can sort it out.

00:40:01.250 --> 00:40:07.000
I think that folks who really
take issue with food trucks

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:12.810
have this like absurd, outdated
mentality about business.

00:40:12.810 --> 00:40:14.690
And they don't really
understand how much

00:40:14.690 --> 00:40:20.560
foot traffic we bring to the
neighborhoods that we visit.

00:40:20.560 --> 00:40:23.485
And I hope he comes, and
we'll do the rap battle.

00:40:23.485 --> 00:40:24.485
We'll get it sorted out.

00:40:24.485 --> 00:40:24.930
AUDIENCE: Looking forward to it.

00:40:24.930 --> 00:40:25.430
Thank you.

00:40:25.430 --> 00:40:28.013
MALE SPEAKER: The truckload of
doughnuts worked with the cops.

00:40:28.013 --> 00:40:29.750
Is it possible
