00:51:11.500 --> 00:51:14.770
ADAM SOBEL: Right, so
so we did a Kickstarter

00:51:14.770 --> 00:51:19.010
for our second truck, which
became the most successful food

00:51:19.010 --> 00:51:22.600
truck-related Kickstarter ever.

00:51:22.600 --> 00:51:26.990
And it was really
out of necessity.

00:51:26.990 --> 00:51:30.120
Without getting too
deeply back into all

00:51:30.120 --> 00:51:34.080
the permit-related
stuff, we were

00:51:34.080 --> 00:51:37.050
waiting on a permit
renewal for our one truck,

00:51:37.050 --> 00:51:38.530
and it was going to take months.

00:51:38.530 --> 00:51:40.090
Because with the
black market we were

00:51:40.090 --> 00:51:43.920
going to have to fly the
permit holder back in Pakistan

00:51:43.920 --> 00:51:45.436
to be there for it.

00:51:45.436 --> 00:51:52.450
And anyway, the easiest way
to be back open in business

00:51:52.450 --> 00:51:56.090
immediately was to buy
somebody else's fully already

00:51:56.090 --> 00:52:00.230
outfitted food truck that
had a permit on it already.

00:52:00.230 --> 00:52:05.320
